&gt;     I stumbled upon this statement
&gt;     &lt;http://stackoverflow.com/a/7632384/285288&gt; that heritirx by default
&gt;     only crawls sites for domains that are in the seeds list. Is that
&gt;     true? I see a lot of google.com &lt;http://google.com&gt;, twitter.com
&gt;     &lt;http://twitter.com&gt; etc. URIs that get crawled, which is not is
&gt;     intended. Which decide rule would be responsible to only crawl
